g.text: Central Furnace: A thick layer of coal dust covers the furnace, colouring it pitch-black.
Inland Empire: Three dangerous stripes appear onto your cheeks, telling stories of your wild soul.
Central Furnace: A hollow ring echoes through the furnace. Your toe hurts.
You: "It gives me confidence and that's all that matters, Kim."
You: "*This* is traditional war-paint. It will grant me safe passage with the spirits that guard this place."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Thank you," the lieutenant nods. "So, where were we?" He turns back to the furnace.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Hmm, maybe you should let your voice rest, officer. Try again later."
Central Furnace: The chatter from the chimney continue on as before. You seem to have made no impression on whatever's *up there*.
Central Furnace: Then again -- maybe it's worth actually trying something *up there*?
You: "I'm not sure, Kim... but I think I can hear someone talking upstairs."
Electrochemistry: Or maybe you're just hungover again.
Endurance: Could it be psychological? Because your physical health is fine.
You: Smear your hands with coal.
Central Furnace: A lush layer of coal now covers your skin, sinking into the wrinkles. Your hands look ancient.
You: No, let's not express ourselves. Let's just wipe our hands clean on our pants.
Inland Empire: Yes, how grown-up. The furnace agrees.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Please wipe your face clean, officer."
Conceptualization: No, you're a proud warrior, keep it.
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant seems relieved as well.
Kim Kitsuragi: "What are you doing?" the lieutenant asks when he sees you climb half-way inside the furnace.
Volition: This sounded real, not imagined.
Central Furnace: "Hello?" you hear a woman's voice answer.
Inland Empire: Looks like this furnace has a face and it's a face of agony.
Authority: You can feel your cheeks turn red under the lieutenant's gaze -- you look like a kid, not a police officer. Even the war-paint can't conceal the embarrassment.
You: "This is the police! Who's there?"
"This is the Remote Viewers Division! Identify yourself!"
You: "Hello! Are you there? Speak to me!"
You: "I summon the ghost of this Doomed Commercial Area. Now begone, vile succubus!"
You: "I summon the ghost of this Doomed Commercial Area. Answer me, spirit!"
Central Furnace: A thick layer of coal dust covers the furnace, colouring it pitch-black.
Central Furnace: Maybe it's coming from behind those safety curtains you saw upstairs? You should investigate...
Central Furnace: Maybe it's coming from somewhere upstairs? You should investigate...
Kim Kitsuragi: "We should ask the lady in the bookstore what's going on with these curtains."
Authority: These three stripes give you strength in this dangerous realm. It would be foolish to remove them.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Okay, sure. Go ahead." He stubbornly looks away from you and the furnace.
Half Light: And it's a woman! Of course! The malicious entities are *always* women.
Authority: What a proud warrior! This is how the hunted becomes the hunter in this dark dangerous place.
You: I'm getting carbon monoxide poisoning.
Physical Instrument: Another pathetic yelp sounds off into the vast darkness of the chimney. You're a little embarrassed you produced it.
Kim Kitsuragi: "What... what are you doing?"
Physical Instrument: Something *breaks loose* in you. A mighty bellow echoes throughout the chimney's depths. The chatter of tiny voices above suddenly cease. Then...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Wait, really?" He looks up at the ceiling. "Maybe it's coming from behind those safety curtains we saw upstairs?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Wait, really?" He looks up at the ceiling. "We should investigate, see if someone's upstairs."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Wait, really?" The lieutenant sounds concerned. "Take your head out of the chimney, please. It's not safe."
Esprit de Corps: It feels safe to know that the lieutenant's got your back, now and always.
Volition: This sounded real, not imagined.
You: Hadramut Karzai! Smear your cheeks black with coal.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Looks like it. Looks like an old central furnace used to heat the building. It's connected to the chimney..." He opens the door and gingerly peeks inside.
Kim Kitsuragi: "No one has used it in ages... No signs of any recent fire, only dead rats."
Central Furnace: "Hello! Did you say anything?" There's a pause. "I can't hear you, please come upstairs! There's a safety curtain on the second floor, I'll open it!"
You: "We're exploring this dark place and I need the protection my war-paint affords."
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant nods, then points upstairs. "After you, officer."
You: "Those voices I heard... Maybe it's the malignant Entity? Plaisance said it lives in a chimney."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You're right, the rooms do look like they're connected. But *malignant Entities* don't exist -- at least not the *supra-natural* kind."
Encyclopedia: Just pointing out -- this is *not* traditional Semenese war-paint. No idea where you got it.
Central Furnace: It's dark and grimy here. In the darkness, you can hear *chatter*. It's coming from above. A voice -- or several voices -- talking to each other, near the smoke chamber upstairs.
Perception (Hearing): The echo is so prominent, it's impossible to discern what the voices are saying. Or what's producing them.
Half Light: Then what was the chatter you heard?
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes. Yes, it was," the lieutenant nods, before turning back to the furnace.
Physical Instrument: You muster all your strength and yell...
Perception (Hearing): You hear a low rumble upstairs -- the sound of a curtain being pulled aside.
Inland Empire: You've awakened the entity!
You: "I am the reincarnation of an ancient Iilmaraan warrior."
You: I hear the murderer of the hanged man talking.
You: Kick it with your foot.
You: "Kim, what is this thing? Is it a furnace?!"
Rhetoric: Always has to be the sceptic, this man...
Physical Instrument: Your dehydrated, hungover throat can produce little more than a dry croak.
Your throat can produce little more than a dry croak. Awkward, since you already had a drink...
You: "Nothing!" (Wipe your face clean.) "Sorry, that was stupid."
"I'm hallucinating. Or maybe it's the Entity..."
You: "I hear the murderer of the hanged man talking."
Conceptualization: Maybe you could *paint* something with this coal? Leave a cave painting for future archaeologists... no, that would be stupid.
Physical Instrument: Still, it's good you have this dirt on you. Real men wear *coal* for make-up.
Inland Empire: You feel the spirit of Ramout Karzai, ancient hero of Graad, pulsing through you. All that's left is to cover your face in war-paint.
Volition: A lifetime of smoking and drinking will do that to you.
